<h1><strong>The Goal</strong></h1>  <p>I'm trying to make a dictionary that stores a key (string) and a value (array) pair in ASP.</p>  <p><strong>The Problem:</strong></p>  <p>It seems that ASP is capable of storing the array as a value and furthermore capable of returning the value (at any point in the array), but it's not capable of updating the value?</p>  <p><strong>What I have</strong></p>  <pre><code>Dim myDict Set myDict=Server.CreateObject("Scripting.Dictionary") </code></pre>  <p>I set the value with:</p>  <pre><code>myDict.add someKey, someArray </code></pre>  <p>I retrieve with:</p>  <pre><code>myDict.Item(someKey)(somePosition) </code></pre>  <p>However, this doesnt work:</p>  <pre><code>myDict.Item(someKey)(somePosition) = "Hello" </code></pre>